  "answer": "The target’s mechanism does not require the Sea Peoples to be purely disorganized refugees. It states they were “displaced populations fleeing ecological stress” whose invasions were “opportunistic.” Organized polities can still be displaced by famine and drought; pre-existing political organization is fully compatible with opportunistic territorial expansion in response to climate-driven collapse of neighboring palace economies. The forbidden case asserts attestation of “organized polities with territorial ambitions” predating the collapses, but the target’s mechanism can accommodate this: drought-induced systemic stress could simultaneously motivate already-organized groups to pursue territorial acquisition as an adaptive strategy, making their invasions both opportunistic and symptomatic of the wider climatic crisis. The causal primacy of the drought is not falsified unless it is shown that the Sea Peoples’ invasions would have occurred with the same timing and effect absent the climatic anomaly—a point the forbidden case does not establish."
